Summary: This document outlines the timetable for the 3rd and 4th semesters of the Master of Technology in Artificial Intelligence Systems program at NUS. The classes will be held on Saturdays from 9:00am to 5:00pm, starting on January 11, 2025 and ending on April 5, 2025. The course will cover topics such as intelligent sensing systems, vision systems, spatial reasoning, and real-time audio-visual sensing and sense making. The course manager is Tian Jing. This information is confidential and was last updated on March 19, 2025.

This page outlines the timetable for the 3rd and 4th semester of the EBA5008 Graduate Certificate in Intelligent Financial Risk Management course. The course will be held on Saturdays from 9:00am to 5:00pm, starting on July 5th, 2025 and ending on October 11th, 2025. The exam period is tentatively scheduled for the 2nd week of November 2025, but may be subject to change. The course will cover topics such as Advanced Machine Learning for Financial Services, Explainable and Responsible AI for Finance, Credit Risk Modelling and Analytics, and Alternative Data for Fintech Innovation.
